# Component Governance Rule

Use this codebase with strict component governance. Do not invent new UI patterns when live equivalents exist.

## Source-of-Truth Priority

When implementing or proposing UI:

1. First reference live pages:
   - `app/page.tsx`
   - `app/casino/page.tsx`
   - `app/sports/page.tsx`
   - `app/sports/football/page.tsx`
2. Then use shared components from `components/*`.
3. Treat `app/library/page.tsx` as an audited catalog only when entries are live-source + audited.

## Hard Rules

- Do not use stale, legacy, or unverified components for new screens.
- Match existing structure, spacing scale, token usage, and interaction behaviors.
- Reuse existing CTA styles, status tags, and motion patterns from live flows.
- New routes must preserve the global page shell used by live pages:
  - main top navigation
  - left side navigation
  - standard footer
- Do not build standalone page layouts that omit these shell regions unless explicitly requested.
- If no verified component exists, explicitly mark as "new pattern required" and request source confirmation.

## Library Governance

- Keep audit lock enforced for library browsing.
- Show only entries that are both:
  - Source-verified (`LIVE_SOURCE_PATHS`)
  - Audited (`AUDITED_ENTRY_IDS`)

## Assistant Behavior

- If asked to create a new page, start from closest live page pattern first.
- For new pages, compose from or re-export an existing live shell page so nav/sidebar/footer remain present by default.
- Never suggest "made-up" components.
- If confidence is low on component provenance, say so and ask for a live source path.
